<title>USA: Bayou Steel settles 3-year labor strike.</title>
<headline>Bayou Steel settles 3-year labor strike.</headline>
<dateline>LAPLACE, La. 1996-09-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Bayou Steel Corp said Monday it and the United Steelworkers of America have ended a three-and-a-half year strike after reaching a binding six-year settlement.</p>
<p>The contract allows Bayou to contract out certain jobs and provides a new health care plan that includes employee contributions. Bayou said the contract ties future labor cost increases to increased company productivity, efficiency, and performance. There is no provision for a guaranteed raise in base pay, the company said.</p>
<p>The company expects a six-week transition before eligible strikers return to work.</p>
